messages.message: Hi Team - AI Hub looks to not be giving me feedback on the document in this screenshot. It says that this is a result of being over 20 pages, but the document is only 4:

did you just run this field? or did this field value already exist when you opened the project?

i’m asking bc this is a reasoning field, and we just GA’d confidence values for reasoning fields in 24.20

oops i forgot, aihub.instabase.com (http://aihub.instabase.com) is still on 24.18, so this feature is in internal preview - i assume you’ve turned on the feature flag for confidence values for reasoning fields?

hmm if you ran it today on 24.18, we’d still expect a confidence value to be shown

i was thinking that maybe you ran it previously on an old release like 24.12, in which case confidence wouldn’t be returned
specifically - under "Financial Statement" -> the "Summary of Stocks" field
hmm it seems that the model is returning confidence as 0.0 - @Sławek Biel do you know why this might happen?

FWIW, I ran into this issue a lot on the tables for this project:
https://aihub.instabase.com/hub/build/018fbee1-9026-7967-9bae-0df5e939fd06

It wasn't consistent though as about a quarter or a third of the tables/docs would display a confidence value.  Only 1 of the files is over 20 pages, and none of the individual documents with that field are over 2 pages.
